/*
this is a more complex(generalized experimental variant 
of [irrationalStride]
https://www.shadertoy.com/results?query=irrationalStride&sort=newest&filter=

for an explanation of THIS shader read text below:
(copied from: https://www.shadertoy.com/view/wdGBDW )

I updated the [stride] shaders to [irrationalStride]
and added a [stride] epxplanation for them in the commonTab of 
https://www.shadertoy.com/view/Xl3BD4

A hairline is a rationalStride, much simpler.
but my code also dares to quantize for irrational ratios
, within a limited PlanckLength.

You may think of a stride input values
as the 2 sizes of strided lists. 
Number of Red and blue cards;
StrideIntuitive(uv,red,blue,offset)

But my function has 2 different inputs, 
tripplet( uv,start,end,(fraction) )
(red==fraction == 3 == constant within the function
, but could be parametric where
, in case of a (non rational) remainder
, RED is always shown, and blue is ommitted/overwritten.

I then generalized this more into:
pmodfM(uv,start,end,fraction,planckPrecision)
of 
https://www.shadertoy.com/view/4ttBD4
pmodfM(...)
should work with float, vec2, vec3 , vec4 inputs

you can use
pmodfM(uv,offset+Red,offset+red+blue,red,planckPrecision)

and for a Jairline, that is
offset=iTime%iResolution
pmodfM(uv.x,offset+1,offset+iResolution.x,1,0.001)

and the precision is really not needed here
, because all other inputs are whole numbers. (?)



tags:
starguitar, irrationalstride, arpshepardtone, ditherhairlinequantize, chromaticscalecordtartanweave
*/


